revisions.description: Initial version of MIB module ACD-SA-MIB.

acdSa.contactinfo: Accedian Technical Assistance Center Accedian Networks, Inc. 4878 Levy, suite 202 Saint-Laurent, Quebec Canada H4R 2P1 E-mail: support@accedian.com
acdSa.description: The Service Availability database for this Accedian Networks device.

AcdSaMetricType.name: AcdSaMetricType
AcdSaMetricType.description: A value that represents a type of metric that can be used in an instance of Service Availability.

AcdSaValidFlag.name: AcdSaValidFlag
AcdSaValidFlag.description: The validity flag can have three values: valid, adjusted, or pending. The value of valid indicates the metrics are calculated normally. The value of adjusted is used to indicate a change occurred in the configuration during the reporting period which may impact the service availability calculation. The value of pending indicates that the counters were reset in the middle of a time interval.

AcdSaAdminStateFlag.name: AcdSaAdminStateFlag
AcdSaAdminStateFlag.description: This flag is used for the administrative state. The value IS indicates the state is In-Service. The value OOS indicates the state is Out-of-Service.

AcdSaOperStateFlag.name: AcdSaOperStateFlag
AcdSaOperStateFlag.description: This flag is used for the operational state. The value IS indicates the state is In-Service. The value OOS indicates the state is Out-of-Service. The value oos-au indicates the state is Out-of-Service-Autonomous. This state is entered when all of the metrics associated with the service instance are disabled.

acdSaServiceConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of all settings for a Service.

acdSaServiceIndex.name: acdSaServiceIndex
acdSaServiceIndex.description: Unique value for each service instance.

acdSaServiceConfigRowStatus.name: acdSaServiceConfigRowStatus
acdSaServiceConfigRowStatus.description: All columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated. To create a new Service you shall provide a unique name for an empty row with the RowStatus set to Create and Go.

acdSaServiceConfigName.name: acdSaServiceConfigName
acdSaServiceConfigName.description: A unique name used to identify the Service.

acdSaServiceConfigReportingPeriod.name: acdSaServiceConfigReportingPeriod
acdSaServiceConfigReportingPeriod.description: A reporting period over which availability counters are evaluated in addition to the monotonic counters (In minutes).

acdSaServiceConfigUaWindowSize.name: acdSaServiceConfigUaWindowSize
acdSaServiceConfigUaWindowSize.description: The number of consecutive seconds over which to assess unavailability.

acdSaServiceConfigHliWindowSize.name: acdSaServiceConfigHliWindowSize
acdSaServiceConfigHliWindowSize.description: The number of consecutive Time Intervals used to assess High Loss Intervals for this instance.

acdSaServiceConfigTimeInterval.name: acdSaServiceConfigTimeInterval
acdSaServiceConfigTimeInterval.description: The interval of time during which the metric is evaluated. Allowed values are 1, 5, 10, 20, or 60.

acdSaMetricConfigEntry.name: acdSaMetricConfigEntry
acdSaMetricConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of all settings for a Metric.

acdSaMetricConfigRowStatus.name: acdSaMetricConfigRowStatus
acdSaMetricConfigRowStatus.description: All columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated. To create a new Service you shall provide the a unique name for an empty row with the RowStatus set to Create and Go. To delete the VLAN set you need to set the RowStatus to destroy.

acdSaMetricConfigName.name: acdSaMetricConfigName
acdSaMetricConfigName.description: A unique name used to identify the Metric.

acdSaMetricConfigSrcName.name: acdSaMetricConfigSrcName
acdSaMetricConfigSrcName.description: A unique name used to identify the source metric.

acdSaMetricConfigType.name: acdSaMetricConfigType
acdSaMetricConfigType.description: Enable or disable the Service Availability entry.

acdSaMetricConfigThreshold.name: acdSaMetricConfigThreshold
acdSaMetricConfigThreshold.description: Indicates the delay threshold for this metric when type is one of metric delay parameters (in micro-seconds). Indicates the packet loss threshold for this metric when type is one of packet-loss parameter expressed in millionth of percent (1,000,000 is 1%).

acdSaServiceCounterEntry.description: An entry consisting of all counters for a Service.

acdSaServiceCounterPeriodIndex.name: acdSaServiceCounterPeriodIndex
acdSaServiceCounterPeriodIndex.description: An index that uniquely identifies the particular sample this entry represents among all samples associated with the same service instance. This index starts at 1 and increases by one as each new period.

acdSaServiceCounterValidFlag.name: acdSaServiceCounterValidFlag
acdSaServiceCounterValidFlag.description: Indicates the validity of the service counter during this sampling interval.

acdSaServiceCounterUpTime.name: acdSaServiceCounterUpTime
acdSaServiceCounterUpTime.description: Uptime is a measure of the time a service has been up during this sampling interval.

acdSaServiceCounterUaTime.name: acdSaServiceCounterUaTime
acdSaServiceCounterUaTime.description: The UaTime is a measure of the time a service has been unavailable during this sampling interval.

acdSaServiceCounterMaintTime.name: acdSaServiceCounterMaintTime
acdSaServiceCounterMaintTime.description: The MaintTime is a measure of the time a service has been in maintenance during this sampling interval.

acdSaServiceCounterAvailRatio.name: acdSaServiceCounterAvailRatio
acdSaServiceCounterAvailRatio.description: Indicates the availability ratio in millionth of a percent (1,000,000 is 1%).

acdSaServiceCounterGaps.name: acdSaServiceCounterGaps
acdSaServiceCounterGaps.description: The gap shall be the number of time the state change from available to unavailable.

acdSaServiceCounterLargestGap.name: acdSaServiceCounterLargestGap
acdSaServiceCounterLargestGap.description: The largest gap shall be the largest number of consecutive unavailable second.

acdSaServiceCounterChliTime.name: acdSaServiceCounterChliTime
acdSaServiceCounterChliTime.description: The CHLI time is a counter which increments for every high loss interval. It is only reset to zero when one of the following conditions occur: 1) device reboot 2) explicit counter reset.

acdSaServiceCounterChliRatio.name: acdSaServiceCounterChliRatio
acdSaServiceCounterChliRatio.description: The ratio of high loss intervals divided by the uptime minus the sum of maintenance time and unavailable time, expressed in millionth of a percent (1,000,000 is 1%).
